Writing providers manually works, but it's verbose. Riverpod Generator reduces boilerplate by 80%:

**Before (manual):**
```dart
final usersProvider = FutureProvider<List<User>>((ref) async {
  final response = await ref.watch(httpClientProvider).get('/users');
  return response.map(User.fromJson).toList();
});
```

**After (with @riverpod):**
```dart
@riverpod
Future<List<User>> users(UsersRef ref) async {
  final response = await ref.watch(httpClientProvider).get('/users');
  return response.map(User.fromJson).toList();
}
```

The generator creates the provider for you!

